    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can have performance implications, especially when used in SELECT statements that process large datasets. Each invocation of the function can result in a separate execution context, which can be costly in terms of CPU and I/O. To mitigate this, consider:"
